name: Everton vs Liverpool
summary: In a thrilling Merseyside derby, Everton emerged victorious over Liverpool 2-0, dealing a significant blow to their rivals' title hopes. The match, which marked Jurgen Klopp's final derby as Liverpool manager, saw Everton take the lead through a well-taken header by Conor Coady. Dwight McNeil sealed the win late in the game with a clinical finish. Liverpool's defeat puts their Premier League title aspirations in jeopardy, while Everton's triumph provides a much-needed boost in their battle against relegation. The match was available for live viewing through various platforms such as Amazon Prime Video, Sky Sports, and ESPN+, and highlighted the intense rivalry and passion that exists in this historic fixture.

name: Where is Gallipoli
summary: From Gallipoli to Gaza, commemorations mark the legacy of the Anzacs, not as a "coming of age" tale but as a lesson for the future. New Zealand musicians faced the disappointment of lost luggage at Gallipoli, leaving them without instruments for Anzac Day. Amidst the tributes, an NZ Army soldier embarked on a pilgrimage to honor his family's sacrifice. Details for Anzac Day services and the traditional Anzac biscuit recipe were shared widely. The often-overlooked roles of Asian troops at Gallipoli are being remembered. The first Anzacs, fighting over 50 years prior, are also being recognized. Personal stories emerge, like that of the two brothers who died together at Gallipoli. A film review assesses "Before Dawn," a World War I drama that falls short of the impact of "Gallipoli." Finally, a horse racing event is named in honor of the Gallipoli Memorial Trophy.

name: Anzac Day parade
summary: On April 25, Australia and New Zealand honor their war dead with dawn services and marches on Anzac Day. Thousands gathered for these events across Australia and New Zealand, including in major cities like Sydney, Melbourne, Brisbane, and Perth. The day commemorates the anniversary of the first major military action fought by Australian and New Zealand forces during World War I at Gallipoli in 1915. Dawn services are held at war memorials and cemeteries to pay respect to those who died in the war. Marches and other events are also held throughout the day to honor the veterans and their families.

name: Arsenal
summary: In the upcoming season, Arsenal are set to replace their iconic club crest with the cannon logo on their uniforms. The club recently celebrated a resounding 5-0 victory over Chelsea, solidifying their position at the top of the Premier League table. Amidst this success, defender Timber expressed his gratitude for his return to the team. Additionally, actress Anne Hathaway has been revealed as a secret Arsenal supporter, adding to the club's growing popularity. However, their title hopes suffered a setback as Aston Villa defeated them 2-0. Despite this, Arsenal regained their dominance with a triumph over Wolves. The team's spirited performance against Chelsea highlighted their prowess, with Kai Havertz and Ben White each scoring twice in the 5-0 win. Analysts predict that Arsenal will continue to be contenders for the Premier League title in the remaining fixtures, although they have bowed out of the Champions League alongside Manchester City.

name: Are shops open on Anzac Day
summary: ANZAC Day trading hours vary across Australia in 2024. In New South Wales, Australian Capital Territory, Victoria, South Australia, and Tasmania, most businesses will be closed on ANZAC Day, including supermarkets like Coles and Woolworths, hardware stores like Bunnings, and shopping centres like Westfield. Some exceptions apply, with some businesses being allowed to trade during specific hours, such as convenience stores, pharmacies, and petrol stations. In Queensland, Western Australia, and the Northern Territory, larger stores are able to trade on Anzac Day, but some smaller stores may choose to close. It is important to check with your local store to confirm its trading hours on ANZAC Day.

name: Capitol
summary: Various news events related to the Capitol are reported in these headlines. The Capitol Centre is getting ready to start its 2024-25 season, showcasing performing arts. DanceFusion's 13th Annual Showcase will take place at the Capitol Theatre. Due to necessary maintenance, Heritage Park trails will be temporarily closed in the Capitol Lake area. Regarding the attack on the US Capitol, a former Connecticut official has received a 10-day prison sentence, while a man who stormed the Capitol with a Confederate flag and assaulted police has received over two years. The Capitol rioters have drawn criticism, with one being convicted based on his own messages and another pleading guilty to assaulting police, including Brian Sicknick. In response to the January 6th incident, President Biden will honor the officers who defended the Capitol with the Citizens Medal. In a separate development, Secretary of Homeland Security Alejandro Mayorkas has returned to Capitol Hill despite the Senate rejecting impeachment charges against him.

name: Gallipoli
summary: Various news articles commemorate Anzac Day while offering diverse perspectives. One article sheds light on the evolving understanding of the Gallipoli campaign, urging it to be seen as a cautionary tale rather than a coming-of-age story. Another highlights the plight of a New Zealand band left without instruments due to lost luggage. The growing recognition of Gurkha and Sikh troops' contributions in World War I is also discussed. A poignant article follows a soldier's pilgrimage to honor his family's legacy at Gallipoli, while another expresses concern over the destruction of an Anzac Cove monument amidst rising Islamist sentiment. Amidst "panic" over lost luggage, the NZDF's reduced role in the Gallipoli dawn service is reported. Other articles announce arrangements for broadcast and imagery coverage of Anzac Day commemorations in Gallipoli and France in 2024. The tragedy of two brothers who fought and died together in Gallipoli is also remembered. Finally, the NZ Defence rallies to fulfill ceremonial roles despite the luggage mishap.

name: Inflation rate Australia
summary: Australia's inflation rate slowed in the first quarter of 2024, disappointing expectations and putting a damper on hopes for an early interest rate cut. Despite the slowdown, the Consumer Price Index (CPI) inflation rate still climbed to 1.0%, exceeding the anticipated 0.8%. This inflation increase has made Australia's inflation rate the highest globally, highlighting the challenge facing the Reserve Bank of Australia (RBA). The higher-than-expected inflation in the March quarter has ruled out any immediate rate cut prospects. The Australian dollar (AUD) gained against the US dollar (USD) following the inflation news, which reinforced the RBA's stance on maintaining high interest rates. However, inflation is gradually decreasing, even as student debt rises, and experts acknowledge the need to rethink rate cuts due to Australia's persistent inflation.
